free-your-disk (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Unified home dashboard with a 3D usage donut and one-click scan.
  * Whole-disk file-type breakdown (incl. caches & dependencies, system,
    reserved) with clickable per-category file lists.
  * Applications section: apt/flatpak/snap/AppImage inventory by size, update
    checking, batch uninstall/update, protected system packages.
  * App & browser cache cleanup (Chromium/Electron, Flatpak, Snap, npm).
  * Disk health tab: SMART via nvme-cli/smartctl + real-time I/O graphs.
  * Light/dark/system theme, language, launch at startup, low-space monitor.
  * Incremental scan engine with instant cached results on open.
  * Accurate du-based system-size measurement with honest reserved-blocks
    accounting.

 -- rony <rony@rlconseil.net>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 18:00:00 +0000

free-your-disk (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * Disk scanning and safe cleanup: temporary files, largest files, git
    worktrees and developer caches.
  * Recoverable-by-default deletion (XDG trash), dry-run preview, Polkit
    helper for privileged cleanup.
  * System tray icon with a disk-usage popover widget.

